<div class="author-biography"><p>Michael T. Klare, a <a href="https://tomdispatch.com/on-the-brink-in-2026/" data-wpel-link="internal"><em>TomDispatch</em> regular</a>, is the five-college professor emeritus of peace and world security studies at Hampshire College and a senior visiting fellow at the Arms Control Association. He is the author of 15 books, the latest of which is <em><a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/1627792481/ref=nosim/?tag=tomdispatch-20" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external">All Hell Breaking Loose: The Pentagon’s Perspective on Climate Change</a></em>. He is a founder of the <a href="https://www.saneuschinapolicy.org/" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="nofollow external noopener noreferrer">Committee for a Sane U.S.-China Policy</a>.</p>
